Male-nia)çš„åå­—ä¸Šã€‚&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="NRNntAWN"&gt;å¦ä¸€ä¸ªå’Œ Virginia é¢‡æœ‰æ¸Šæºçš„å¯¹è±¡æ˜¯ã€ŒçŒ©çº¢è…è´¥ã€å…¨é¢çˆ†å‘æ—¶ç››æ”¾çš„ã€Œè‰¾å¥¥å°¼äºšä¹‹èŠ±ã€ï¼Œ&lt;a href="https://link.zhihu.com/?target=https%3A//www.reddit.com/r/Eldenring/comments/u3z1xw/malenias_second_phase_appears_to_be_based_on/" class=" wrap external" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;Reddit&lt;/a&gt; ä¸Šå¾ˆæ—©å°±æœ‰ç”¨æˆ·æŒ‡å‡ºã€Œç›è²å¦®äºšå¼€å‡ºçš„çŒ©çº¢è‰¾å¥¥å°¼äºšä¹‹èŠ±ï¼Œå…¶è®¾å®šå¤§æ¦‚æ˜¯åŸºäºçœŸèŒçš„ä¸€ä¸ªå±â€”â€”èƒ¶é”ˆèŒå±ã€ï¼š&lt;/p&gt;&lt;figure data-size="normal"&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic2.zhimg.com/v2-ce43260401437f90a0c5701c96280b4d_b.jpg" data-size="normal" data-rawwidth="1110" data-rawheight="1324" class="origin_image zh-lightbox-thumb" width="1110" data-original="https://pic2.zhimg.com/v2-ce43260401437f90a0c5701c96280b4d_r.jpg" data-original-token="v2-ce43260401437f90a0c5701c96280b4d"/&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;ç¡®å®æ—¢è§†æ„Ÿå¾ˆå¼º&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;p data-pid="bPolN-lZ"&gt;&lt;a href="https://link.zhihu.com/?target=https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gymnosporangium" class=" wrap external" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;Wiki&lt;/a&gt; ä¸Šæ˜¯è¿™ä¹ˆä»‹ç»çš„ï¼š&lt;/p&gt;&lt;blockquote data-pid="KcsBhRKi"&gt;Gymnosporangium is a genus of heteroecious plant-pathogenic fungi which alternately infect members of the family Cupressaceae, primarily species in the genus Juniperus (junipers), and members of the family Rosaceae in the subfamily Amygdaloideae (apples, pears, quinces, shadbush, hawthorns, rowans and their relatives). The common name cedar-apple rusts has been used for these fungi. According to the Dictionary of the Fungi (10th edition, 2008), there are about 57 species in the genus.&lt;br/&gt;In junipers (the primary hosts, see photo), some species form a ball-like gall about 2â€“4 cm in diameter which produces a set of &lt;b&gt;orange tentacle-like spore tubes&lt;/b&gt; called &lt;b&gt;telial horns&lt;/b&gt;. These horns expand and have a jelly like consistency when wet. In other species, such as in G. clarvariforme, the telia are produced directly from the bark of the juniper with no obvious gall formation or swelling. The basidiospores are released and travel on the wind until they infect an apple, pear, hawthorn or suitable tree.&lt;br/&gt;On the secondary hosts, the fungus produces yellowish depressions on the leaves. &lt;b&gt;It also infects the fruit, which grows whitish tubes like a Medusa head.&lt;/b&gt; These are the spore tubes. &lt;b&gt;These aeciospores must then infect a juniper to complete the life cycle. &lt;/b&gt;All the types of spores can spread over long distances.&lt;br/&gt;ã€ä¸­æ–‡ç¿»è¯‘ã€‘â†“ (SANå€¼é™ä½è­¦å‘Šï¼å¦å¤–ï¼Œåˆ«æ‰‹è´±å»æœå›¾â€¦â€¦)&lt;br/&gt;Gymnosporangium æ˜¯å¼‚ç§æ¤ç‰©ç—…åŸçœŸèŒçš„ä¸€ä¸ªå±ï¼Œå®ƒè½®æµæ„ŸæŸ“æŸç§‘æˆå‘˜(ä¸»è¦æ˜¯åˆºæŸå±ä¸‹çš„ç‰©ç§)ï¼Œä»¥åŠæä»äºšç§‘çš„è”·è–‡ç§‘æˆå‘˜(è‹¹æœã€æ¢¨ã€æ¦…æ¡²ã€å”æ££ã€å±±æ¥‚ã€èŠ±æ¥¸åŠå…¶è¿‘äº²)ã€‚è¿™äº›çœŸèŒçš„é€šç”¨åä¸ºé›ªæ¾-è‹¹æœé”ˆç—…ã€å…¶å®ä¸å‡†ç¡®ï¼Œå› ä¸ºåˆºæŸä¸¥æ ¼æ¥è¯´ä¸æ˜¯é›ªæ¾ã€‘ã€‚æ ¹æ®ã€ŠçœŸèŒè¯å…¸ã€‹(2008å¹´ç¬¬10ç‰ˆ)ï¼Œè¯¥å±çº¦æœ‰57ç§ã€‚&lt;br/&gt;åœ¨åˆºæŸå±æ¤ç‰©(åŸç”Ÿå®¿ä¸»ï¼Œè§å›¾ã€å…¶å® Reddit é‚£ä¸ªå›¾é‡Œå°±æ˜¯ã€‘)ä¸­ï¼Œä¸€äº›ç‰©ç§ä¼šå½¢æˆç›´å¾„çº¦2-4å˜ç±³çš„çƒçŠ¶ç˜¿ï¼Œå¹¶äº§ç”Ÿä¸€ç»„&lt;b&gt;æ©™è‰²çš„è§¦æ‰‹çŠ¶å­¢å­ç®¡&lt;/b&gt;ï¼Œç§°ä¸º &lt;b&gt;Telial è§’&lt;/b&gt;ã€‚ è¿™äº›è§’åœ¨æ½®æ¹¿æ—¶ä¼šè†¨èƒ€ï¼Œå¹¶å…·æœ‰æœå†»æ ·çš„ç²˜ç¨ åº¦ã€‚åœ¨å…¶ä»–ç‰©ç§ï¼Œå¦‚ G. clarvariforme ä¸­, telia æ˜¯ç›´æ¥ä»åˆºæŸæ ‘çš®äº§ç”Ÿçš„ï¼Œæ²¡æœ‰æ˜æ˜¾çš„ç˜¿å½¢æˆæˆ–è‚¿èƒ€ã€‚æ‹…å­¢å­è¢«é‡Šæ”¾åä¼šéšé£ä¼ æ’­ï¼Œç›´åˆ°æ„ŸæŸ“è‹¹æœã€æ¢¨ã€å±±æ¥‚æˆ–å…¶ä»–åˆé€‚çš„æ ‘ã€‚  &lt;br/&gt;åœ¨æ¬¡ç”Ÿå®¿ä¸»ä¸Šï¼ŒçœŸèŒåœ¨å¶ç‰‡ä¸Šäº§ç”Ÿæ·¡é»„è‰²çš„å‡¹é™·ã€‚&lt;b&gt;å®ƒè¿˜ä¼šæ„ŸæŸ“æœå®ï¼Œä½¿æœå®é•¿å‡ºä¸€å †ç™½è‰²çš„ç®¡çŠ¶ç‰©ï¼Œå°±åƒç¾æœèçš„å¤´ä¸€æ ·ã€‚&lt;/b&gt;è¿™äº›å°±æ˜¯å­¢å­ç®¡ã€‚ &lt;b&gt;æ¥ç€è¿™äº›å­¢å­å¿…é¡»æ„ŸæŸ“åˆºæŸæ¥å®Œæˆæ•´ä¸ªç”Ÿå‘½å‘¨æœŸã€‚&lt;/b&gt; æ‰€æœ‰ç±»å‹çš„å­¢å­éƒ½å¯ä»¥é•¿è·ç¦»ä¼ æ’­ã€‚  &lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;p data-pid="fndZfyTg"